"{\"uid\": \"bangkokpost.com-opinion-opinion-3203860-killing-the-goose-that-lays-the-olympic-gold-medal\", \"noun_phrases\": [{\"sentence\": \"PUBLISHED : 24 Feb 2026 at 01:01 NEWSPAPER SECTION:Oped WRITER:Nancy Qian The Olympic Games have always been about more than sports, with the medal count serving as a measure of national vitality.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 199, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 65, \"end\": 75, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nancy_Qian\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Nancy Qian\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nancy_Qian\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nancy_Qian\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"PUBLISHED\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 9}, {\"ngram\": \"24 Feb\", \"from\": 12, \"to\": 18}, {\"ngram\": \"01:01 NEWSPAPER SECTION\", \"from\": 27, \"to\": 50}, {\"ngram\": \"Oped WRITER\", \"from\": 51, \"to\": 62}, {\"ngram\": \"sports\", \"from\": 125, \"to\": 131}, {\"ngram\": \"the medal count\", \"from\": 138, \"to\": 153}, {\"ngram\": \"a measure\", \"from\": 165, \"to\": 174}, {\"ngram\": \"national vitality\", \"from\": 178, \"to\": 195}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The 2026 Winter Games in Milan and Cortina are no different.\", \"from\": 200, \"to\": 260, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 225, \"end\": 230, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Milan\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.912116651532224e-13, \"text\": \"Milan\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Milan\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Milan\"}, {\"begin\": 235, \"end\": 242, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cortina_d'Ampezzo\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 7.084912534912364e-15, \"text\": \"Cortina\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cortina_d'Ampezzo\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cortina_d'Ampezzo\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The 2026 Winter Games\", \"from\": 200, \"to\": 221}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The Americans, like everyone else, want confirmation of their preeminence.\", \"from\": 261, \"to\": 335, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 261, \"end\": 274, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Americans\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 7.521198423976376e-18, \"text\": \"The Americans\", \"types\": [\"Q386724\", \"Q15416\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Americans\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Americans\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"everyone\", \"from\": 281, \"to\": 289}, {\"ngram\": \"confirmation\", \"from\": 301, \"to\": 313}, {\"ngram\": \"their preeminence\", \"from\": 317, \"to\": 334}]}, {\"sentence\": \"So important is that outcome that even US Vice President JD Vance briefly acknowledged the value of non-white immigration to the United States when he complained that Eileen Gu, the US-born medal-winning skier for China, should be competing under the American flag.\", \"from\": 336, \"to\": 601, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 375, \"end\": 392, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Vice_President_of_the_United_States\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"US Vice President\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Vice_President_of_the_United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Vice_President_of_the_United_States\"}, {\"begin\": 393, \"end\": 395, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/JD.com\", \"score\": 0.997291053398998, \"rank\": 0.0027163049226543953, \"text\": \"JD\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/JD.com\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/JD.com\"}, {\"begin\": 396, \"end\": 401, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Zebulon_Baird_Vance\", \"score\": 0.9999999997999112, \"rank\": 1.9981325910202012e-10, \"text\": \"Vance\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Zebulon_Baird_Vance\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Zebulon_Baird_Vance\"}, {\"begin\": 465, \"end\": 478, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.999999998716703, \"rank\": 1.2834552082976486e-09, \"text\": \"United States\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}, {\"begin\": 503, \"end\": 512, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Eileen_Gu\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Eileen Gu\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Eileen_Gu\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Eileen_Gu\"}, {\"begin\": 550, \"end\": 555, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"score\": 0.9999999986703187, \"rank\": 9.199211406432813e-10, \"text\": \"China\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\"}, {\"begin\": 587, \"end\": 600, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Flag_of_the_United_States\", \"score\": 0.9999999999972715, \"rank\": 2.7723609622134803e-12, \"text\": \"American flag\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Flag_of_the_United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Flag_of_the_United_States\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"that outcome\", \"from\": 352, \"to\": 364}, {\"ngram\": \"the value\", \"from\": 423, \"to\": 432}, {\"ngram\": \"non-white immigration\", \"from\": 436, \"to\": 457}, {\"ngram\": \"the US-born medal-winning skier\", \"from\": 514, \"to\": 545}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But the medal table is just one scoreboard.\", \"from\": 603, \"to\": 646, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the medal table\", \"from\": 607, \"to\": 622}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Beyond the ice rink and the slopes is a much larger and more consequential contest for excellence, namely in scientific leadership, technological supremacy, and geopolitical influence.\", \"from\": 647, \"to\": 831, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the ice rink\", \"from\": 654, \"to\": 666}, {\"ngram\": \"the slopes\", \"from\": 671, \"to\": 681}, {\"ngram\": \"a much larger and more consequential contest\", \"from\": 685, \"to\": 729}, {\"ngram\": \"excellence\", \"from\": 734, \"to\": 744}, {\"ngram\": \"scientific leadership\", \"from\": 756, \"to\": 777}, {\"ngram\": \"technological supremacy\", \"from\": 779, \"to\": 802}, {\"ngram\": \"geopolitical influence\", \"from\": 808, \"to\": 830}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Here, too, China is most portrayed as America's nemesis, with the future of each at stake.\", \"from\": 832, \"to\": 922, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 843, \"end\": 848, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"score\": 0.9999999986703187, \"rank\": 9.199211406432813e-10, \"text\": \"China\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"America's nemesis\", \"from\": 870, \"to\": 887}, {\"ngram\": \"the future\", \"from\": 894, \"to\": 904}, {\"ngram\": \"stake\", \"from\": 916, \"to\": 921}]}, {\"sentence\": \"And here, too, there is a question about what role immigrants -- like Gu's Chinese mother -- should play.\", \"from\": 923, \"to\": 1028, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 998, \"end\": 1005, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"score\": 0.9935181973684333, \"rank\": 0.004989661959523509, \"text\": \"Chinese\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a question\", \"from\": 947, \"to\": 957}, {\"ngram\": \"what role immigrants\", \"from\": 964, \"to\": 984}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Although immigrants bring talent and ambition, they also might compete for jobs or disseminate US-acquired knowledge abroad.\", \"from\": 1029, \"to\": 1153, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"immigrants\", \"from\": 1038, \"to\": 1048}, {\"ngram\": \"talent\", \"from\": 1055, \"to\": 1061}, {\"ngram\": \"ambition\", \"from\": 1066, \"to\": 1074}, {\"ngram\": \"jobs\", \"from\": 1104, \"to\": 1108}, {\"ngram\": \"US-acquired knowledge\", \"from\": 1124, \"to\": 1145}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Owing to these concerns, the US has tightened its immigration policies in recent years, even restricting highly skilled professionals.\", \"from\": 1154, \"to\": 1288, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1183, \"end\": 1185, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9999999896635927, \"rank\": 9.872117045628285e-09, \"text\": \"US\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"these concerns\", \"from\": 1163, \"to\": 1177}, {\"ngram\": \"its immigration policies\", \"from\": 1200, \"to\": 1224}, {\"ngram\": \"recent years\", \"from\": 1228, \"to\": 1240}, {\"ngram\": \"highly skilled professionals\", \"from\": 1259, \"to\": 1287}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Such measures reflect a fundamental misunderstanding of how countries compete for global pre-eminence -- and the Olympics reveal why.\", \"from\": 1290, \"to\": 1423, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Such measures\", \"from\": 1290, \"to\": 1303}, {\"ngram\": \"a fundamental misunderstanding\", \"from\": 1312, \"to\": 1342}, {\"ngram\": \"countries\", \"from\": 1350, \"to\": 1359}, {\"ngram\": \"eminence\", \"from\": 1383, \"to\": 1391}, {\"ngram\": \"the Olympics\", \"from\": 1399, \"to\": 1411}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Consider figure skating, one of the most visible winter sports.\", \"from\": 1424, \"to\": 1487, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"figure skating\", \"from\": 1433, \"to\": 1447}, {\"ngram\": \"the most visible winter sports\", \"from\": 1456, \"to\": 1486}]}, {\"sentence\": \"For decades, the US has crowded the podium with the children of immigrants: Michelle Kwan (silver, 1998; bronze, 2002), Sasha Cohen (silver, 2006), Mirai Nagasu (bronze, 2018, team), Nathan Chen (gold, 2022), and, this winter, Ilia Malinin (gold, 2026, team) and Alysa Liu (gold, 2026).\", \"from\": 1488, \"to\": 1774, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1505, \"end\": 1507, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9999999896635927, \"rank\": 9.872117045628285e-09, \"text\": \"US\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}, {\"begin\": 1564, \"end\": 1572, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Michelle_Obama\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.2596191972457502e-13, \"text\": \"Michelle\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Michelle_Obama\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Michelle_Obama\"}, {\"begin\": 1608, \"end\": 1619, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sasha_Cohen\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Sasha Cohen\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q13219587\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sasha_Cohen\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sasha_Cohen\"}, {\"begin\": 1636, \"end\": 1648, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mirai_Nagasu\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Mirai Nagasu\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q13219587\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mirai_Nagasu\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mirai_Nagasu\"}, {\"begin\": 1671, \"end\": 1682, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nathan_Chen\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Nathan Chen\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q13219587\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nathan_Chen\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nathan_Chen\"}, {\"begin\": 1715, \"end\": 1727, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ilia_Malinin\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Ilia Malinin\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q13219587\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ilia_Malinin\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ilia_Malinin\"}, {\"begin\": 1751, \"end\": 1760, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alysa_Liu\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Alysa Liu\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q13219587\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alysa_Liu\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alysa_Liu\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"decades\", \"from\": 1492, \"to\": 1499}, {\"ngram\": \"the podium\", \"from\": 1520, \"to\": 1530}, {\"ngram\": \"the children\", \"from\": 1536, \"to\": 1548}, {\"ngram\": \"immigrants\", \"from\": 1552, \"to\": 1562}, {\"ngram\": \"silver\", \"from\": 1579, \"to\": 1585}, {\"ngram\": \"bronze\", \"from\": 1593, \"to\": 1599}, {\"ngram\": \"silver\", \"from\": 1621, \"to\": 1627}, {\"ngram\": \"(bronze\", \"from\": 1649, \"to\": 1656}, {\"ngram\": \"team\", \"from\": 1664, \"to\": 1668}, {\"ngram\": \"gold\", \"from\": 1684, \"to\": 1688}, {\"ngram\": \"this winter\", \"from\": 1702, \"to\": 1713}, {\"ngram\": \"gold\", \"from\": 1729, \"to\": 1733}, {\"ngram\": \"team\", \"from\": 1741, \"to\": 1745}, {\"ngram\": \"gold\", \"from\": 1762, \"to\": 1766}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The same is true in other sports.\", \"from\": 1775, \"to\": 1808, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"other sports\", \"from\": 1795, \"to\": 1807}]}, {\"sentence\": \"For example, the speed skater Apolo Ohno (gold, 2002, 2006; eight medals total) has a Japanese-born father, and the snowboarder Chloe Kim (gold, 2018; gold, 2022; silver, 2026) is the daughter of South Korean immigrants.\", \"from\": 1809, \"to\": 2029, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1839, \"end\": 1849, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Apolo_Ohno\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Apolo Ohno\", \"types\": [\"Q847400\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Apolo_Ohno\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Apolo_Ohno\"}, {\"begin\": 1937, \"end\": 1946, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chloe_Kim\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Chloe Kim\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chloe_Kim\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chloe_Kim\"}, {\"begin\": 2011, \"end\": 2028, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Korean_diaspora\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Korean immigrants\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Korean_diaspora\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Korean_diaspora\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"example\", \"from\": 1813, \"to\": 1820}, {\"ngram\": \"gold\", \"from\": 1851, \"to\": 1855}, {\"ngram\": \"eight medals\", \"from\": 1869, \"to\": 1881}, {\"ngram\": \"a Japanese-born father\", \"from\": 1893, \"to\": 1915}, {\"ngram\": \"the snowboarder\", \"from\": 1921, \"to\": 1936}, {\"ngram\": \"gold\", \"from\": 1948, \"to\": 1952}, {\"ngram\": \"gold\", \"from\": 1960, \"to\": 1964}, {\"ngram\": \"silver\", \"from\": 1972, \"to\": 1978}, {\"ngram\": \"the daughter\", \"from\": 1989, \"to\": 2001}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The list grows longer if one includes champions descended from earlier migration waves, such as Polish-American Tara Lipinski (gold, 1998) and Japanese-American Kristi Yamaguchi (gold, 1992).\", \"from\": 2031, \"to\": 2222, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2127, \"end\": 2142, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Polish_Americans\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.4675564384838277e-21, \"text\": \"Polish-American\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Polish_Americans\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Polish_Americans\"}, {\"begin\": 2143, \"end\": 2156, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/