ion international students study in the US each year -- accounting for about 6% of total higher-education enrolment -- and they are concentrated in STEM and quantitative fields.\", \"from\": 2367, \"to\": 2560, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2423, \"end\": 2425, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9999999896635927, \"rank\": 9.872117045628285e-09, \"text\": \"US\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}, {\"begin\": 2531, \"end\": 2535, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Women_in_STEM_fields\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.2565196978318876e-27, \"text\": \"STEM\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Women_in_STEM_fields\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Women_in_STEM_fields\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Roughly 1.2 million international students\", \"from\": 2367, \"to\": 2409}, {\"ngram\": \"about 6%\", \"from\": 2454, \"to\": 2462}, {\"ngram\": \"total higher-education enrolment\", \"from\": 2466, \"to\": 2498}]}, {\"sentence\": \"For example, foreign nationals account for 82% of full-time graduate students in petroleum engineering, 74% in electrical engineering, 72% in computer and information sciences, 71% in industrial and manufacturing engineering, 70% in statistics, 67% in economics, 61% in civil engineering, 58% in mechanical engineering and agricultural economics, 56% in mathematics, 54% in chemical engineering, 53% in metallurgical and materials engineering, 52% in materials sciences, and 50% in pharmaceutical sciences.\", \"from\": 2561, \"to\": 3067, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"example\", \"from\": 2565, \"to\": 2572}, {\"ngram\": \"foreign nationals\", \"from\": 2574, \"to\": 2591}, {\"ngram\": \"82%\", \"from\": 2604, \"to\": 2607}, {\"ngram\": \"full-time graduate students\", \"from\": 2611, \"to\": 2638}, {\"ngram\": \"petroleum engineering\", \"from\"