engineers\", \"from\": 3140, \"to\": 3159}, {\"ngram\": \"founders\", \"from\": 3161, \"to\": 3169}, {\"ngram\": \"patent holders\", \"from\": 3175, \"to\": 3189}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Some see this as a source of American strength, whereas critics warn of leakage.\", \"from\": 3191, \"to\": 3271, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3220, \"end\": 3228, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9999412026742442, \"rank\": 5.88007830271657e-05, \"text\": \"American\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a source\", \"from\": 3208, \"to\": 3216}, {\"ngram\": \"critics\", \"from\": 3247, \"to\": 3254}, {\"ngram\": \"leakage\", \"from\": 3263, \"to\": 3270}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In fact, talent flows both ways.\", \"from\": 3272, \"to\": 3304, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"fact\", \"from\": 3275, \"to\": 3279}, {\"ngram\": \"talent\", \"from\": 3281, \"to\": 3287}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Among Olympians, for example, the figure skater Deanna Stellato-Dudek was born and trained in the US but now competes for Canada.\", \"from\": 3305, \"to\": 3434, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3353, \"end\": 3374, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Deanna_Stellato\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Deanna Stellato-Dudek\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q13219587\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Deanna_Stellato\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Deanna_Stellato\"}, {\"begin\": 3403, \"end\": 3405, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9999999896635927, \"rank\": 9.872117045628285e-09, \"text\": \"US\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}, {\"begin\": 3427, \"end\": 3433, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canada\", \"score\": 0.9999999697465687, \"rank\": 2.966068553593304e-08, \"text\": \"Canada\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canada\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canada\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Olympians\", \"from\": 3311, \"to\": 3320}, {\"ngram\": \"example\", \"from\": 3326, \"to\": 3333}]}, {\"sentence\": \"More controversially, China reportedly allocated substantial state funding to recruit US-trained athletes such as Gu (who has now won five Olympic medals for her sponsor) and Zhu Yi before the 2022 Beijing Games.\", \"from\": 3435, \"to\": 3647, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3457, \"end\": 3462, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"score\": 0.9999999986703187, \"rank\": 9.199211406432813e-10, \"text\": \"China\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\"}, {\"begin\": 3610, \"end\": 3616, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Zhu_Yi_(Eastern_Wu)\", \"score\": 0.8425919415519253, \"rank\": 0.14835164835157091, \"text\": \"Zhu Yi\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Zhu_Yi_(Eastern_Wu)\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Zhu_Yi_(Eastern_Wu)\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"substantial state funding\", \"from\": 3484, \"to\": 3509}, {\"ngram\": \"US-trained athletes\", \"from\": 3521, \"to\": 3540}, {\"ngram\": \"Gu\", \"from\": 3549, \"to\": 3551}, {\"ngram\": \"five Olympic medals\", \"from\": 3569, \"to\": 3588}, {\"ngram\": \"her sponsor\", \"from\": 3593, \"to\": 3604}, {\"ngram\": \"the 2022 Beijing Games\", \"from\": 3624, \"to\": 3646}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It is not surprising that such moves fuel anxiety in the US.\", \"from\": 3648, \"to\": 3708, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3705, \"end\": 3707, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9999999896635927, \"rank\": 9.872117045628285e-09, \"text\": \"US\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}], \"noun_phrases\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"But a sense of perspective is in order.\", \"from\": 3709, \"to\": 3748, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a sense\", \"from\": 3713, \"to\": 3720}, {\"ngram\": \"perspective\", \"from\": 3724, \"to\": 3735}, {\"ngram\": \"order\", \"from\": 3742, \"to\": 3747}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The US won 25 medals at the Beijing Olympics in 2022, compared to China's 15, and this gap will be even wider in 2026.\", \"from\": 3749, \"to\": 3867, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3753, \"end\": 3755, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9999999896635927, \"rank\": 9.872117045628285e-09, \"text\": \"US\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"25 medals\", \"from\": 3760, \"to\": 3769}, {\"ngram\": \"the Beijing Olympics\", \"from\": 3773, \"to\": 3793}, {\"ngram\": \"this gap\", \"from\": 3831, \"to\": 3839}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Evidently, the benefits of attracting foreign talent outweigh the costs.\", \"from\": 3868, \"to\": 3940, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the benefits\", \"from\": 3879, \"to\": 3891}, {\"ngram\": \"foreign talent\", \"from\": 3906, \"to\": 3920}, {\"ngram\": \"the costs\", \"from\": 3930, \"to\": 3939}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The same lesson holds in science, where the US has been the world's leading source of Nobel laureates.\", \"from\": 3942, \"to\": 4044, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3986, \"end\": 3988, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9999999896635927, \"rank\": 9.872117045628285e-09, \"text\": \"US\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The same lesson\", \"from\": 3942, \"to\": 3957}, {\"ngram\": \"science\", \"from\": 3967, \"to\": 3974}, {\"ngram\": \"the world's leading source\", \"from\": 3998, \"to\": 4024}, {\"ngram\": \"Nobel laureates\", \"from\": 4028, \"to\": 4043}]}, {\"sentence\": \"American institutions have captured about 40% of science Nobels since 1945, and over half of economics Nobels since 1969.\", \"from\": 4045, \"to\": 4166, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4045, \"end\": 4053, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9999412026742442, \"rank\": 5.88007830271657e-05, \"text\": \"American\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"about 40%\", \"from\": 4081, \"to\": 4090}, {\"ngram\": \"science Nobels\", \"from\": 4094, \"to\": 4108}, {\"ngram\": \"half\", \"from\": 4130, \"to\": 4134}, {\"ngram\": \"economics Nobels\", \"from\": 4138, \"to\": 4154}]}, {\"sentence\": \"America's prize-winning edge has been deeply intertwined with immigration.\", \"from\": 4167, \"to\": 4241, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"America's prize-winning edge\", \"from\": 4167, \"to\": 4195}, {\"ngram\": \"immigration\", \"from\": 4229, \"to\": 4240}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Roughly 40% of US-affiliated Nobel laureates in physics, chemistry, and physiology or medicine have been foreign-born.\", \"from\": 4242, \"to\": 4360, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Roughly 40%\", \"from\": 4242, \"to\": 4253}, {\"ngram\": \"US-affiliated Nobel laureates\", \"from\": 4257, \"to\": 4286}, {\"ngram\": \"physics\", \"from\": 4290, \"to\": 4297}, {\"ngram\": \"chemistry\", \"from\": 4299, \"to\": 4308}, {\"ngram\": \"physiology\", \"from\": 4314, \"to\": 4324}, {\"ngram\": \"medicine\", \"from\": 4328, \"to\": 4336}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Many of the private-sector architects of America's most important strategic technologies were also born abroad.\", \"from\": 4361, \"to\": 4472, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the private-sector architects\", \"from\": 4369, \"to\": 4398}, {\"ngram\": \"America's most important strategic technologies\", \"from\": 4402, \"to\": 4449}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Sergey Brin, born in the Soviet Union, co-founded Google.\", \"from\": 4473, \"to\": 4530, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4473, \"end\": 4484, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sergey_Brin\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Sergey Brin\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sergey_Brin\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sergey_Brin\"}, {\"begin\": 4505, \"end\": 4510, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.505893750861092e-25, \"text\": \"Union\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}, {\"begin\": 4523, \"end\": 4529, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Google\", \"score\": 0.9999988650267443, \"rank\": 1.1345455497752912e-06, \"text\": \"Google\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Google\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Google\"}], \"noun_phrases\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Elon Musk, born in South Africa, built Tesla and SpaceX.\", \"from\": 4531, \"to\": 4587, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4531, \"end\": 4540, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Elon_Musk\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Elon Musk\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Elon_Musk\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Elon_Musk\"}, {\"begin\": 4550, \"end\": 4562, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Africa\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 6.9266090436572805e-18, \"text